-- India Takes 192-Run Over Australia in Test After Dhoni Hits 224
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2013-02-25T05:08:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-25/india-takes-192-run-over-australia-in-test-after-dhoni-hits-224.html
India made 572 in reply to
 Australia ’s first-innings 380 on day four of their series-
opening cricket Test in Chennai as home captain Mahendra Singh Dhoni struck 224.  Dhoni’s 265-ball innings, which included 24 fours and six
sixes, was the third-highest score by a wicketkeeper in elite
Tests. It ended when he gloved a catch behind off a delivery
from  James Pattinson , who finished as Australia’s best bowler
with 5-96. Spin bowler Nathan Lyon took 3-215 in 47 overs.  India added 57 runs in about an hour after resuming day
four on 515-8.  The teams are scheduled to play four Tests, with matches
following in Hyderabad, Mohali and Delhi.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  